    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 5: \"The adaptor protein Fe65 (APBB1) is present in Schaffer collaterals/CA1 dendritic spine hippocampal synapses where it colocalizes with P2X2 subunits. Immunogold localization of Fe65 using Fe65-32 (A-C) or Fe65-35 (D-G) antibodies. Gold particles were found both at the pre- and postsynaptic specialization of excitatory hippocampal synapses.\". Experimental description: M&M: \"Light and Electron Microscopy\nFour postnatal day 35 Sprague-Dawley rats were transcardially perfused. \"\n\nantibody:\n\"Polyclonal antibodies were raised in rabbits using the GST fusion protein containing amino acids 197-255 or amino acids 40-100 of Fe65 (antibodies Fe65-32 or -35, respectively).\"",
